{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":920,"text":"Most of you can probably relate\nto what I'm feeling right now."},{"time":5172,"text":"My heart is racing in my chest."},{"time":7895,"text":"My palms are a little bit clammy."},{"time":10856,"text":"I'm sweating."},{"time":12823,"text":"And my breath is a little bit shallow."},{"time":15498,"text":"Now, these familiar sensations\nare obviously the result"},{"time":18382,"text":"of standing up\nin front of a thousand of you"},{"time":20789,"text":"and giving a talk\nthat might be streamed online"},{"time":23074,"text":"to perhaps a million more."},{"time":25266,"text":"But the physical sensations\nI'm experiencing right now"},{"time":27869,"text":"are actually the result of a much more\nbasic mind-body mechanism."},{"time":32398,"text":"My nervous system is sending\na flood of hormones"},{"time":35725,"text":"like cortisol and adrenaline\ninto my bloodstream."},{"time":39233,"text":"It's a very old and very necessary\nresponse that sends blood and oxygen"},{"time":44022,"text":"to the organs and muscles\nthat I might need"},{"time":46125,"text":"to respond quickly to a potential threat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49206,"text":"But there's a problem with this response,"},{"time":51260,"text":"and that is, it can get over-activated."},{"time":54414,"text":"If I face these kinds of stressors\non a daily basis,"},{"time":57448,"text":"particularly over an extended\nperiod of time,"},{"time":60891,"text":"my system can get overloaded."},{"time":63595,"text":"So basically, if this response\nhappens infrequently: super-necessary"},{"time":67288,"text":"for my well-being and survival."},{"time":69564,"text":"But if it happens too much,"},{"time":71125,"text":"it can actually make me sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73750,"text":"There's a growing body of research\nexamining the relationship"},{"time":76683,"text":"between chronic stress and illness."},{"time":78793,"text":"Things like heart disease and even cancer"},{"time":80906,"text":"are being shown to have\na relationship to stress."},{"time":83974,"text":"And that's because, over time,\ntoo much activation from stress"},{"time":88014,"text":"can interfere with my body's processes\nthat keep me healthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92973,"text":"Now, let's imagine for a moment\nthat I was pregnant."},{"time":96606,"text":"What might this kind of stress,"},{"time":98577,"text":"particularly over the length\nof my pregnancy,"},{"time":100870,"text":"what kind of impact might that have"},{"time":102734,"text":"on the health of my developing fetus?"},{"time":106356,"text":"You probably won't be surprised\nwhen I tell you"},{"time":108717,"text":"that this kind of stress\nduring pregnancy is not good."},{"time":112115,"text":"It can even cause the body\nto initiate labor too early,"},{"time":115770,"text":"because in a basic sense,\nthe stress communicates"},{"time":118460,"text":"that the womb is no longer\na safe place for the child."},{"time":122351,"text":"Stress during pregnancy is linked\nwith things like high blood pressure"},{"time":125734,"text":"and low infant birth weight,"},{"time":127417,"text":"and it can begin a cascade\nof health challenges"},{"time":129633,"text":"that make birth much more dangerous"},{"time":131820,"text":"for both parent and child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135134,"text":"Now of course stress,\nparticularly in our modern lifestyle,"},{"time":138210,"text":"is a somewhat universal experience, right?"},{"time":140524,"text":"Maybe you've never stood up\nto give a TED Talk,"},{"time":142888,"text":"but you've faced a big\npresentation at work,"},{"time":145566,"text":"a sudden job loss,"},{"time":147158,"text":"a big test,"},{"time":148495,"text":"a heated conflict\nwith a family member or friend."},{"time":151936,"text":"But it turns out that the kind\nof stress we experience"},{"time":155096,"text":"and whether we're able to stay\nin a relaxed state long enough"},{"time":158334,"text":"to keep our bodies working properly"},{"time":160409,"text":"depends a lot on who we are."},{"time":163435,"text":"There's also a growing body of research"},{"time":165320,"text":"showing that people who experience\nmore discrimination"},{"time":169322,"text":"are more likely to have poor health."},{"time":172021,"text":"Even the threat of discrimination,"},{"time":174335,"text":"like worrying you might be stopped\nby police while driving your car,"},{"time":177801,"text":"can have a negative impact on your health."},{"time":182867,"text":"Harvard Professor Dr. David Williams,"},{"time":185470,"text":"the person who pioneered\nthe tools that have proven these linkages,"},{"time":188961,"text":"says that the more marginalized\ngroups in our society"},{"time":191938,"text":"experience more discrimination\nand more impacts on their health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196702,"text":"I've been interested in these issues\nfor over a decade."},{"time":199838,"text":"I became interested in maternal health"},{"time":202670,"text":"when a failed premed trajectory\ninstead sent me down a path"},{"time":206439,"text":"looking for other ways\nto help pregnant people."},{"time":208932,"text":"I became a doula,"},{"time":210380,"text":"a lay person trained to provide support"},{"time":212427,"text":"to people during pregnancy and childbirth."},{"time":214571,"text":"And because I'm Latina\nand a Spanish speaker,"},{"time":217179,"text":"in my first volunteer doula gig\nat a public hospital in North Carolina,"},{"time":221112,"text":"I saw clearly how race and class\nimpacted the experiences"},{"time":224459,"text":"of the women that I supported."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226849,"text":"If we take a look at the statistics\nabout the rates of illness"},{"time":230208,"text":"during pregnancy and childbirth,"},{"time":232035,"text":"we see clearly the pattern\noutlined by Dr. Williams."},{"time":235713,"text":"African-American women in particular"},{"time":237986,"text":"have an entirely different\nexperience than white women"},{"time":240919,"text":"when it comes to whether\ntheir babies are born healthy."},{"time":244488,"text":"In certain parts of the country,\nparticularly the Deep South,"},{"time":247596,"text":"the rates of mother\nand infant death for black women"},{"time":250333,"text":"actually approximate\nthose rates in Sub-Saharan African."},{"time":254820,"text":"In those same communities,"},{"time":256465,"text":"the rates for white women are near zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260720,"text":"Even nationally, black women\nare four times more likely"},{"time":264339,"text":"to die during pregnancy and childbirth"},{"time":266655,"text":"than white women."},{"time":268252,"text":"Four times more likely to die."},{"time":271272,"text":"They're also twice as likely\nfor their infants to die"},{"time":274215,"text":"before the first year of life"},{"time":275820,"text":"than white infants,"},{"time":277375,"text":"and two to three times more likely"},{"time":279316,"text":"to give birth too early or too skinny --"},{"time":282256,"text":"a sign of insufficient development."},{"time":284917,"text":"Native women are also more likely\nto have higher rates of these problems"},{"time":289058,"text":"than white women,"},{"time":290280,"text":"as are some groups of Latinas."},{"time":293325,"text":"For the last decade as a doula\nturned journalist and blogger,"},{"time":296310,"text":"I've been trying to raise the alarm"},{"time":298049,"text":"about just how different\nthe experiences of women of color,"},{"time":301044,"text":"but particularly black women,"},{"time":302523,"text":"are when it comes to pregnancy\nand birth in the US."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305346,"text":"But when I tell people\nabout these appalling statistics,"},{"time":308266,"text":"I'm usually met with an assumption\nthat it's about either poverty"},{"time":312021,"text":"or lack of access to care."},{"time":314221,"text":"But it turns out, neither of these things\ntell the whole story."},{"time":317568,"text":"Even middle-class black women\nstill have much worse outcomes"},{"time":322104,"text":"than their middle-class\nwhite counterparts."},{"time":325062,"text":"The gap actually widens among this group."},{"time":328554,"text":"And while access to care\nis definitely still a problem,"},{"time":332097,"text":"even women of color who receive\nthe recommended prenatal care"},{"time":335560,"text":"still suffer from these high rates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338429,"text":"And so we come back to the path"},{"time":340308,"text":"from discrimination to stress\nto poor health,"},{"time":344483,"text":"and it begins to paint a picture\nthat many people of color know to be true:"},{"time":348704,"text":"racism is actually making us sick."},{"time":352288,"text":"Still sound like a stretch?"},{"time":353976,"text":"Consider this: immigrants,\nparticularly black and Latina immigrants,"},{"time":358284,"text":"actually have better health when\nthey first arrive in the United States."},{"time":361847,"text":"But the longer they stay in this country,\nthe worse their health becomes."},{"time":366436,"text":"People like me, born in the United States\nto Cuban immigrant parents,"},{"time":370572,"text":"are actually more likely to have\nworse health than my grandparents did."},{"time":374729,"text":"It's what researchers call\n\"the immigrant paradox,\""},{"time":377255,"text":"and it further illustrates"},{"time":378563,"text":"that there's something\nin the US environment"},{"time":380790,"text":"that is making us sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382680,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":383869,"text":"this problem, that racism\nis making people of color,"},{"time":386960,"text":"but especially black\nwomen and babies, sick, is vast."},{"time":389665,"text":"I could spend all of my time\nwith you talking about it,"},{"time":392459,"text":"but I won't, because I want to make sure\nto tell you about one solution."},{"time":396138,"text":"And the good news is, it's a solution\nthat isn't particularly expensive,"},{"time":399595,"text":"and doesn't require\nany fancy drug treatments"},{"time":402085,"text":"or new technologies."},{"time":403295,"text":"The solution is called, \"The JJ Way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":407489,"text":"Meet Jennie Joseph."},{"time":409425,"text":"She's a midwife\nin the Orlando, Florida area"},{"time":411996,"text":"who has been serving\npregnant women for over a decade."},{"time":415252,"text":"In what she calls her easy-access clinics,"},{"time":417693,"text":"Jennie and her team provide prenatal care\nto over 600 women per year."},{"time":422872,"text":"Her clients, most of whom are black,\nHaitian and Latina,"},{"time":427623,"text":"deliver at the local hospital."},{"time":429621,"text":"But by providing accessible\nand respectful prenatal care,"},{"time":433672,"text":"Jennie has achieved something remarkable:"},{"time":436196,"text":"almost all of her clients give birth\nto healthy, full-term babies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441465,"text":"Her method is deceptively simple."},{"time":443876,"text":"Jennie says that all of her appointments\nstart at the front desk."},{"time":447076,"text":"Every member of her team,\nand every moment a women is at her clinic,"},{"time":450840,"text":"is as supportive as possible."},{"time":453393,"text":"No one is turned away\ndue to lack of funds."},{"time":455819,"text":"The JJ Way is to make the finances work\nno matter what the hurdles."},{"time":459980,"text":"No one is chastised for showing up\nlate to their appointments."},{"time":462998,"text":"No one is talked down to or belittled."},{"time":465774,"text":"Jennie's waiting room feels more like\nyour aunt's living room than a clinic."},{"time":470035,"text":"She calls this space\n\"a classroom in disguise.\""},{"time":473692,"text":"With the plush chairs\narranged in a circle,"},{"time":476115,"text":"women wait for their appointments\nin one-on-one chats"},{"time":478799,"text":"with a staff educator,"},{"time":480056,"text":"or in group prenatal classes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482749,"text":"When you finally are called back\nto your appointment,"},{"time":485308,"text":"you are greeted by Alexis or Trina,"},{"time":487179,"text":"two of Jennie's medical assistants."},{"time":489092,"text":"Both are young, African-American\nand moms themselves."},{"time":492635,"text":"Their approach is casual and friendly."},{"time":495305,"text":"During one visit I observed,"},{"time":497104,"text":"Trina chatted with a young soon-to-be mom"},{"time":500055,"text":"while she took her blood pressure."},{"time":501950,"text":"This Latina mom was having trouble\nkeeping food down due to nausea."},{"time":506365,"text":"As Trina deflated the blood pressure cuff,"},{"time":508437,"text":"she said, \"We'll see about changing\nyour prescription, OK?"},{"time":511279,"text":"We can't have you not eating.\""},{"time":513711,"text":"That \"we\" is actually a really crucial\naspect of Jennie's model."},{"time":517784,"text":"She sees her staff as part of a team that,\nalongside the woman and her family,"},{"time":522567,"text":"has one goal:"},{"time":523965,"text":"get mom to term with a healthy baby."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527269,"text":"Jennie says that Trina and Alexis\nare actually the center of her care model,"},{"time":530982,"text":"and that her role as a provider\nis just to support their work."},{"time":535350,"text":"Trina spends a lot of her day\non her cell phone,"},{"time":537648,"text":"texting with clients\nabout all sorts of things."},{"time":540084,"text":"One woman texted to ask if a medication\nshe was prescribed at the hospital"},{"time":543985,"text":"was OK to take while pregnant."},{"time":545947,"text":"The answer was no."},{"time":547648,"text":"Another woman texted with pictures\nof an infant born under Jennie's care."},{"time":552519,"text":"Lastly, when you finally are called back\nto see the provider,"},{"time":555874,"text":"you've already taken your own weight\nin the waiting room,"},{"time":558627,"text":"and done your own pee test\nin the bathroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561029,"text":"This is a big departure\nfrom the traditional medical model,"},{"time":563892,"text":"because it places\nresponsibility and information"},{"time":566804,"text":"back in the woman's hands."},{"time":569139,"text":"So rather than a medical setting\nwhere you might be chastised"},{"time":572100,"text":"for not keeping up\nwith provider recommendations --"},{"time":574576,"text":"the kind of settings often available\nto low-income women --"},{"time":577646,"text":"Jennie's model is to be\nas supportive as possible."},{"time":581177,"text":"And that support provides a crucial buffer"},{"time":584218,"text":"to the stress of racism and discrimination\nfacing these women every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590188,"text":"But here's the best thing\nabout Jennie's model:"},{"time":593399,"text":"it's been incredibly successful."},{"time":596375,"text":"Remember those statistics I told you,"},{"time":598210,"text":"that black women are more likely\nto give birth too early,"},{"time":600990,"text":"to give birth to low birth weight babies,"},{"time":603166,"text":"to even die due to complications\nof pregnancy and childbirth?"},{"time":606720,"text":"Well, The JJ Way has almost entirely\neliminated those problems,"},{"time":610609,"text":"starting with what Jennie calls\n\"skinny babies.\""},{"time":613672,"text":"She's been able to get almost all\nher clients to term"},{"time":616294,"text":"with healthy, chunky babies like this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619948,"text":"Audience: Aw!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":622320,"text":"Miriam Zoila Pérez:\nThis is a baby girl"},{"time":624601,"text":"born to a client of Jennie's\nthis past June."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627974,"text":"A similar demographic\nof women in Jennie's area"},{"time":630592,"text":"who gave birth at the same\nhospital her clients did"},{"time":633488,"text":"were three times more likely to give birth"},{"time":636100,"text":"to a baby below a healthy weight."},{"time":638857,"text":"Jennie is making headway\ninto what has been seen for decades"},{"time":641939,"text":"as an almost intractable problem."},{"time":645108,"text":"Some of you might be thinking,"},{"time":646798,"text":"all this one-on-one attention\nthat The JJ Way requires"},{"time":649443,"text":"must be too expensive to scale."},{"time":651802,"text":"Well, you'd be wrong."},{"time":653282,"text":"The visit with the provider\nis not the center of Jennie's model,"},{"time":656889,"text":"and for good reason."},{"time":658444,"text":"Those visits are expensive,\nand in order to maintain her model,"},{"time":661569,"text":"she's got to see a lot\nof clients to cover costs."},{"time":664086,"text":"But Jennie doesn't have to spend\na ton of time with each woman,"},{"time":667203,"text":"if all of the members of her team\ncan provide the support, information"},{"time":671649,"text":"and care that her clients need."},{"time":674730,"text":"The beauty of Jennie's model\nis that she actually believes"},{"time":677769,"text":"it can be implemented\nin pretty much any health care setting."},{"time":681008,"text":"It's a revolution in care\njust waiting to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685405,"text":"These problems I've been sharing\nwith you are big."},{"time":687869,"text":"They come from long histories\nof racism, classism,"},{"time":691305,"text":"a society based on race\nand class stratification."},{"time":694217,"text":"They involve elaborate\nphysiological mechanisms"},{"time":696637,"text":"meant to protect us,"},{"time":697816,"text":"that, when overstimulated,\nactually make us sick."},{"time":700756,"text":"But if there's one thing I've learned\nfrom my work as a doula,"},{"time":703742,"text":"it's that a little bit of unconditional\nsupport can go a really long way."},{"time":707608,"text":"History has shown that people\nare incredibly resilient,"},{"time":710501,"text":"and while we can't eradicate racism"},{"time":712408,"text":"or the stress that results\nfrom it overnight,"},{"time":714694,"text":"we might just be able to create\nenvironments that provide a buffer"},{"time":717918,"text":"to what people of color\nexperience on a daily basis."},{"time":720804,"text":"And during pregnancy,\nthat buffer can be an incredible tool"},{"time":724058,"text":"towards shifting the impact of racism"},{"time":726251,"text":"for generations to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728122,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729358,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}